47class BuildFlags : public base::ContextualClass<BuildFlags> {
48 public:
49 BuildFlags() {
50 build_flags_["V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE"] = V8_EXTERNAL_CODE_SPACE_BOOL;
51 build_flags_["TAGGED_SIZE_8_BYTES"] = TargetArchitecture::TaggedSize() == 8;
52#ifdef V8_INTL_SUPPORT
53 build_flags_["V8_INTL_SUPPORT"] = true;
54#else
55 build_flags_["V8_INTL_SUPPORT"] = false;
56#endif
57 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY"] =
58 V8_ENABLE_SWISS_NAME_DICTIONARY_BOOL;
59#ifdef V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS
60 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS"] = true;
61#else
62 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_JAVASCRIPT_PROMISE_HOOKS"] = false;
63#endif
64#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA
65 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA"] = true;
66#else
67 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_CONTINUATION_PRESERVED_EMBEDDER_DATA"] = false;
68#endif
69 build_flags_["TRUE_FOR_TESTING"] = true;
70 build_flags_["FALSE_FOR_TESTING"] = false;
71#ifdef V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME
72 build_flags_["V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME"] = true;
73#else
74 build_flags_["V8_SCRIPTORMODULE_LEGACY_LIFETIME"] = false;
75#endif
76#ifdef V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY
77 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY"] = true;
78#else
79 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_WEBASSEMBLY"] = false;
80#endif
81 build_flags_["V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX"] = V8_ENABLE_SANDBOX_BOOL;
82 build_flags_["DEBUG"] = DEBUG_BOOL;
83 }
84 static bool GetFlag(const std::string& name, const char* production) {
85 auto it = Get().build_flags_.find(name);
86 if (it == Get().build_flags_.end()) {
87 ReportError("Unknown flag used in ", production, ": ", name,
88 ". Please add it to the list in BuildFlags.");
89 }
90 return it->second;
91 }

93 private:
94 std::unordered_map<std::string, bool> build_flags_;

359Expression* MakeCall(IdentifierExpression* callee,
360 base::Optional<Expression*> target,
361 std::vector<Expression*> arguments,
362 const std::vector<Statement*>& otherwise) {
363 std::vector<Identifier*> labels;
364
365 // All IdentifierExpressions are treated as label names and can be directly
366 // used as labels identifiers. All other statements in a call's otherwise
367 // must create intermediate Labels for the otherwise's statement code.
368 size_t label_id_count = 0;
369 std::vector<TryHandler*> temp_labels;
370 for (auto* statement : otherwise) {
371 if (auto* e = ExpressionStatement::DynamicCast(statement)) {
372 if (auto* id = IdentifierExpression::DynamicCast(e->expression)) {
373 if (!id->generic_arguments.empty()) {
374 ReportError("An otherwise label cannot have generic parameters");
375 }
376 labels.push_back(id->name);
377 continue;
378 }
379 }
380 auto label_name = std::string("__label") + std::to_string(label_id_count++);
381 auto label_id = MakeNode<Identifier>(label_name);
382 label_id->pos = SourcePosition::Invalid();
383 labels.push_back(label_id);
384 auto* handler =
385 MakeNode<TryHandler>(TryHandler::HandlerKind::kLabel, label_id,
386 ParameterList::Empty(), statement);
387 temp_labels.push_back(handler);
388 }
389
390 // Create nested try-label expression for all of the temporary Labels that
391 // were created.
392 Expression* result = nullptr;
393 if (target) {
394 result = MakeNode<CallMethodExpression>(*target, callee, arguments, labels);
395 } else {
396 result = MakeNode<CallExpression>(callee, arguments, labels);
397 }
398
399 for (auto* label : temp_labels) {
400 result = MakeNode<TryLabelExpression>(result, label);
401 }
402 return result;
403}

405Expression* MakeCall(Identifier* callee,
406 const std::vector<TypeExpression*>& generic_arguments,
407 const std::vector<Expression*>& arguments,
408 const std::vector<Statement*>& otherwise) {
409 return MakeCall(MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(callee, generic_arguments),
410 base::nullopt, arguments, otherwise);

486void AddParameter(ParameterList* parameter_list,
487 const NameAndTypeExpression& param) {
488 if (!IsLowerCamelCase(param.name->value)) {

495template <bool has_varargs, bool has_explicit_parameter_names>
496base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeParameterList(
497 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
498 auto implicit_params =
499 child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<ImplicitParameters>>();
500 ParameterList result;
501 result.has_varargs = has_varargs;
502 result.implicit_count = 0;
503 result.implicit_kind = ImplicitKind::kNoImplicit;
504 if (implicit_params) {
505 result.implicit_count = implicit_params->parameters.size();
506 if (implicit_params->kind->value == "implicit") {
507 result.implicit_kind = ImplicitKind::kImplicit;
508 } else {
509 DCHECK_EQ(implicit_params->kind->value, "js-implicit");
510 result.implicit_kind = ImplicitKind::kJSImplicit;
511 }
512 result.implicit_kind_pos = implicit_params->kind->pos;
513 for (NameAndTypeExpression& implicit_param : implicit_params->parameters) {
514 AddParameter(&result, implicit_param);
515 }
516 }
517 if (has_explicit_parameter_names) {
518 auto explicit_params =
519 child_results->NextAs<std::vector<NameAndTypeExpression>>();
520 std::string arguments_variable = "";
521 if (has_varargs) {
522 arguments_variable = child_results->NextAs<std::string>();
523 }
524 for (NameAndTypeExpression& param : explicit_params) {
525 AddParameter(&result, param);
526 }
527 result.arguments_variable = arguments_variable;
528 } else {
529 auto explicit_types = child_results->NextAs<TypeList>();
530 for (auto* explicit_type : explicit_types) {
531 result.types.push_back(explicit_type);
532 }
533 }
534 return ParseResult{std::move(result)};
535}

537base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeAssertStatement(
538 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
539 auto kind_string = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>()->value;
540 auto expr_with_source = child_results->NextAs<ExpressionWithSource>();
541 AssertStatement::AssertKind kind;
542 if (kind_string == "dcheck") {
543 kind = AssertStatement::AssertKind::kDcheck;
544 } else if (kind_string == "check") {
545 kind = AssertStatement::AssertKind::kCheck;
546 } else if (kind_string == "static_assert") {
547 kind = AssertStatement::AssertKind::kStaticAssert;
548 } else {
549 UNREACHABLE();
550 }
551 Statement* result = MakeNode<AssertStatement>(
552 kind, expr_with_source.expression, expr_with_source.source);
553 return ParseResult{result};
554}

560 Statement* result = MakeNode<DebugStatement>(

562 : DebugStatement::Kind::kDebug);
563 return ParseResult{result};

575base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeExternalMacro(
576 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
577 auto transitioning = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
578 auto operator_name = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
579 auto external_assembler_name =
580 child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
581 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
582 auto generic_parameters = child_results->NextAs<GenericParameters>();
583 LintGenericParameters(generic_parameters);
584
585 auto args = child_results->NextAs<ParameterList>();
586 auto return_type = child_results->NextAs<TypeExpression*>();
587 auto labels = child_results->NextAs<LabelAndTypesVector>();
588
589 Declaration* result = MakeNode<ExternalMacroDeclaration>(
590 transitioning,
591 external_assembler_name ? *external_assembler_name : "CodeStubAssembler",
592 name, operator_name, args, return_type, labels);
593 if (!generic_parameters.empty()) {
594 Error("External builtins cannot be generic.");
595 }
596 return ParseResult{result};
597}

599base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeIntrinsicDeclaration(
600 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
601 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
602 auto generic_parameters = child_results->NextAs<GenericParameters>();
603 LintGenericParameters(generic_parameters);
604
605 auto args = child_results->NextAs<ParameterList>();
606 auto return_type = child_results->NextAs<TypeExpression*>();
607 auto body = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<Statement*>>();
608 LabelAndTypesVector labels;
609 CallableDeclaration* declaration;
610 if (body) {
611 declaration = MakeNode<TorqueMacroDeclaration>(
612 false, name, base::Optional<std::string>{}, args, return_type, labels,
613 false, body);
614 } else {
615 declaration = MakeNode<IntrinsicDeclaration>(name, args, return_type);
616 }
617 Declaration* result = declaration;
618 if (!generic_parameters.empty()) {
619 result =
620 MakeNode<GenericCallableDeclaration>(generic_parameters, declaration);
621 }
622 return ParseResult{result};
623}

626bool HasAnnotation(ParseResultIterator* child_results, const char* annotation,
627 const char* declaration) {
628 auto annotations = child_results->NextAs<std::vector<Annotation>>();
629 if (!annotations.empty()) {
630 if (annotations.size() > 1 || annotations[0].name->value != annotation) {
631 Error(declaration, " declarations only support a single ", annotation,
632 " annotation");
633 }
634 return true;
635 }
636 return false;
637}

645base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeTorqueMacroDeclaration(
646 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
647 bool export_to_csa = HasExportAnnotation(child_results, "macro");
648 auto transitioning = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
649 auto operator_name = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
650 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
651 if (!IsUpperCamelCase(name->value)) {
652 NamingConventionError("Macro", name, "UpperCamelCase");
653 }
654
655 auto generic_parameters = child_results->NextAs<GenericParameters>();
656 LintGenericParameters(generic_parameters);
657
658 auto args = child_results->NextAs<ParameterList>();
659 auto return_type = child_results->NextAs<TypeExpression*>();
660 auto labels = child_results->NextAs<LabelAndTypesVector>();
661 auto body = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<Statement*>>();
662 CallableDeclaration* declaration = MakeNode<TorqueMacroDeclaration>(
663 transitioning, name, operator_name, args, return_type, labels,
664 export_to_csa, body);
665 Declaration* result = declaration;
666 if (generic_parameters.empty()) {
667 if (!body) ReportError("A non-generic declaration needs a body.");
668 } else {
669 if (export_to_csa) ReportError("Cannot export generics to CSA.");
670 result =
671 MakeNode<GenericCallableDeclaration>(generic_parameters, declaration);
672 }
673 return ParseResult{result};
674}

739base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeAbstractTypeDeclaration(
740 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
741 bool use_parent_type_checker = HasAnnotation(
742 child_results, ANNOTATION_USE_PARENT_TYPE_CHECKER, "abstract type");
743 auto transient = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
744 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
745 if (!IsValidTypeName(name->value)) {
746 NamingConventionError("Type", name, "UpperCamelCase");
747 }
748 auto generic_parameters = child_results->NextAs<GenericParameters>();
749 auto extends = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<TypeExpression*>>();
750 auto generates = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
751 AbstractTypeFlags flags(AbstractTypeFlag::kNone);
752 if (transient) flags |= AbstractTypeFlag::kTransient;
753 if (use_parent_type_checker) flags |= AbstractTypeFlag::kUseParentTypeChecker;
754 TypeDeclaration* type_decl = MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
755 name, flags, extends, std::move(generates));
756 Declaration* decl = type_decl;
757 if (!generic_parameters.empty()) {
758 decl = MakeNode<GenericTypeDeclaration>(generic_parameters, type_decl);
759 }
760
761 auto constexpr_generates =
762 child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
763 std::vector<Declaration*> result{decl};
764
765 if (constexpr_generates) {
766 // Create a AbstractTypeDeclaration for the associated constexpr type.
767 Identifier* constexpr_name =
768 MakeNode<Identifier>(CONSTEXPR_TYPE_PREFIX + name->value);
769 constexpr_name->pos = name->pos;
770
771 base::Optional<TypeExpression*> constexpr_extends;
772 if (extends) {
773 constexpr_extends = AddConstexpr(*extends);
774 }
775 TypeDeclaration* constexpr_decl = MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
776 constexpr_name, flags | AbstractTypeFlag::kConstexpr, constexpr_extends,
777 constexpr_generates);
778 constexpr_decl->pos = name->pos;
779 decl = constexpr_decl;
780 if (!generic_parameters.empty()) {
781 decl =
782 MakeNode<GenericTypeDeclaration>(generic_parameters, constexpr_decl);
783 }
784 result.push_back(decl);
785 }
786
787 return ParseResult{result};
788}

809class AnnotationSet {
810 public:
811 AnnotationSet(ParseResultIterator* iter,
812 const std::set<std::string>& allowed_without_param,
813 const std::set<std::string>& allowed_with_param) {
814 auto list = iter->NextAs<std::vector<Annotation>>();
815 for (const Annotation& a : list) {
816 if (a.param.has_value()) {
817 if (allowed_with_param.find(a.name->value) ==
818 allowed_with_param.end()) {
819 const char* error_message =
820 allowed_without_param.find(a.name->value) ==
821 allowed_without_param.end()
822 ? " is not allowed here"
823 : " cannot have parameter here";
824 Lint("Annotation ", a.name->value, error_message)
825 .Position(a.name->pos);
826 }
827 if (!map_.insert({a.name->value, {*a.param, a.name->pos}}).second) {
828 Lint("Duplicate annotation ", a.name->value).Position(a.name->pos);
829 }
830 } else {
831 if (allowed_without_param.find(a.name->value) ==
832 allowed_without_param.end()) {
833 const char* error_message =
834 allowed_with_param.find(a.name->value) == allowed_with_param.end()
835 ? " is not allowed here"
836 : " requires a parameter here";
837 Lint("Annotation ", a.name->value, error_message)
838 .Position(a.name->pos);
839 }
840 if (!set_.insert(a.name->value).second) {
841 Lint("Duplicate annotation ", a.name->value).Position(a.name->pos);
842 }
843 }
844 }
845 }
846
847 bool Contains(const std::string& s) const {
848 return set_.find(s) != set_.end();
849 }
850 base::Optional<std::string> GetStringParam(const std::string& s) const {
851 auto it = map_.find(s);
852 if (it == map_.end()) {
853 return {};
854 }
855 if (it->second.first.is_int) {
856 Error("Annotation ", s, " requires a string parameter but has an int")
857 .Position(it->second.second);
858 }
859 return it->second.first.string_value;
860 }
861 base::Optional<int32_t> GetIntParam(const std::string& s) const {
862 auto it = map_.find(s);
863 if (it == map_.end()) {
864 return {};
865 }
866 if (!it->second.first.is_int) {
867 Error("Annotation ", s, " requires an int parameter but has a string")
868 .Position(it->second.second);
869 }
870 return it->second.first.int_value;
871 }
872
873 private:
874 std::set<std::string> set_;
875 std::map<std::string, std::pair<AnnotationParameter, SourcePosition>> map_;
876};

878bool ProcessIfAnnotation(ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
879 AnnotationSet annotations(child_results, {},
880 {ANNOTATION_IF, ANNOTATION_IFNOT});
881 if (base::Optional<std::string> condition =
882 annotations.GetStringParam(ANNOTATION_IF)) {
883 if (!BuildFlags::GetFlag(*condition, ANNOTATION_IF)) return false;
884 }
885 if (base::Optional<std::string> condition =
886 annotations.GetStringParam(ANNOTATION_IFNOT)) {
887 if (BuildFlags::GetFlag(*condition, ANNOTATION_IFNOT)) return false;
888 }
889 return true;
890}

892base::Optional<ParseResult> YieldInt32(ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
893 std::string value = child_results->matched_input().ToString();
894 size_t num_chars_converted = 0;
895 int result = 0;
896 try {
897 result = std::stoi(value, &num_chars_converted, 0);
898 } catch (const std::invalid_argument&) {
899 Error("Expected an integer");
900 return ParseResult{result};
901 } catch (const std::out_of_range&) {
902 Error("Integer out of 32-bit range");
903 return ParseResult{result};
904 }
905 // Tokenizer shouldn't have included extra trailing characters.
906 DCHECK_EQ(num_chars_converted, value.size());
907 return ParseResult{result};
908}

910base::Optional<ParseResult> YieldDouble(ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
911 std::string value = child_results->matched_input().ToString();
912 size_t num_chars_converted = 0;
913 double result = 0;
914 try {
915 result = std::stod(value, &num_chars_converted);
916 } catch (const std::out_of_range&) {
917 Error("double literal out-of-range");
918 return ParseResult{result};
919 }
920 // Tokenizer shouldn't have included extra trailing characters.
921 DCHECK_EQ(num_chars_converted, value.size());
922 return ParseResult{result};
923}

925base::Optional<ParseResult> YieldIntegerLiteral(
926 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
927 std::string value = child_results->matched_input().ToString();
928 // Consume a leading minus.
929 bool negative = false;
930 if (!value.empty() && value[0] == '-') {
931 negative = true;
932 value = value.substr(1);
933 }
934 uint64_t absolute_value;
935 try {
936 size_t parsed = 0;
937 absolute_value = std::stoull(value, &parsed, 0);
938 DCHECK_EQ(parsed, value.size());
939 } catch (const std::invalid_argument&) {
940 Error("integer literal could not be parsed").Throw();
941 } catch (const std::out_of_range&) {
942 Error("integer literal value out of range").Throw();
943 }
944 return ParseResult(IntegerLiteral(negative, absolute_value));
945}

985base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeClassDeclaration(
986 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
987 AnnotationSet annotations(
988 child_results,
989 {ANNOTATION_ABSTRACT, ANNOTATION_HAS_SAME_INSTANCE_TYPE_AS_PARENT,
990 ANNOTATION_DO_NOT_GENERATE_CPP_CLASS, ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_CPP_CLASS,
991 ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_MAP, ANNOTATION_GENERATE_BODY_DESCRIPTOR,
992 ANNOTATION_EXPORT, ANNOTATION_DO_NOT_GENERATE_CAST,
993 ANNOTATION_GENERATE_UNIQUE_MAP, ANNOTATION_GENERATE_FACTORY_FUNCTION,
994 ANNOTATION_HIGHEST_INSTANCE_TYPE_WITHIN_PARENT,
995 ANNOTATION_LOWEST_INSTANCE_TYPE_WITHIN_PARENT,
996 ANNOTATION_CPP_OBJECT_DEFINITION,
997 ANNOTATION_CPP_OBJECT_LAYOUT_DEFINITION},
998 {ANNOTATION_RESERVE_BITS_IN_INSTANCE_TYPE,
999 ANNOTATION_INSTANCE_TYPE_VALUE});
1000 ClassFlags flags = ClassFlag::kNone;
1001 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_ABSTRACT)) {
1002 flags |= ClassFlag::kAbstract;
1003 }
1004 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_HAS_SAME_INSTANCE_TYPE_AS_PARENT)) {
1005 flags |= ClassFlag::kHasSameInstanceTypeAsParent;
1006 }
1007 bool do_not_generate_cpp_class =
1008 annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_DO_NOT_GENERATE_CPP_CLASS);
1009 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_CPP_CLASS)) {
1010 Error(
1011 "@customCppClass is deprecated. Use 'extern' instead. "
1012 "@generateBodyDescriptor, @generateUniqueMap, and "
1013 "@generateFactoryFunction accomplish most of what '@export "
1014 "@customCppClass' used to.");
1015 }
1016 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_MAP)) {
1017 Error(
1018 "@customMap is deprecated. Generating a unique map is opt-in now using "
1019 "@generateUniqueMap.");
1020 }
1021 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_DO_NOT_GENERATE_CAST)) {
1022 flags |= ClassFlag::kDoNotGenerateCast;
1023 }
1024 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_GENERATE_BODY_DESCRIPTOR)) {
1025 flags |= ClassFlag::kGenerateBodyDescriptor;
1026 }
1027 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_GENERATE_UNIQUE_MAP)) {
1028 flags |= ClassFlag::kGenerateUniqueMap;
1029 }
1030 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_GENERATE_FACTORY_FUNCTION)) {
1031 flags |= ClassFlag::kGenerateFactoryFunction;
1032 }
1033 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_EXPORT)) {
1034 flags |= ClassFlag::kExport;
1035 }
1036 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_HIGHEST_INSTANCE_TYPE_WITHIN_PARENT)) {
1037 flags |= ClassFlag::kHighestInstanceTypeWithinParent;
1038 }
1039 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_LOWEST_INSTANCE_TYPE_WITHIN_PARENT)) {
1040 flags |= ClassFlag::kLowestInstanceTypeWithinParent;
1041 }
1042 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_OBJECT_DEFINITION)) {
1043 flags |= ClassFlag::kCppObjectDefinition;
1044 }
1045 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_OBJECT_LAYOUT_DEFINITION)) {
1046 flags |= ClassFlag::kCppObjectLayoutDefinition;
1047 }
1048
1049 auto is_extern = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
1050 if (is_extern) flags |= ClassFlag::kExtern;
1051 auto transient = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
1052 if (transient) flags |= ClassFlag::kTransient;
1053 std::string kind = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>()->value;
1054 if (kind == "shape") {
1055 flags |= ClassFlag::kIsShape;
1056 flags |= ClassFlag::kTransient;
1057 flags |= ClassFlag::kHasSameInstanceTypeAsParent;
1058 flags |= ClassFlag::kDoNotGenerateCast;
1059 } else {
1060 DCHECK_EQ(kind, "class");
1061 }
1062 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
1063 if (!IsValidTypeName(name->value)) {
1064 NamingConventionError("Type", name, "UpperCamelCase");
1065 }
1066 auto extends = child_results->NextAs<TypeExpression*>();
1067 if (!BasicTypeExpression::DynamicCast(extends)) {
1068 ReportError("Expected type name in extends clause.");
1069 }
1070 auto generates = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
1071 auto body = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<ClassBody*>>();
1072 std::vector<Declaration*> methods;
1073 std::vector<ClassFieldExpression> fields_raw;
1074 if (body.has_value()) {
1075 methods = (*body)->methods;
1076 fields_raw = (*body)->fields;
1077 } else {
1078 flags |= ClassFlag::kUndefinedLayout;
1079 }
1080
1081 if (is_extern && body.has_value()) {
1082 if (!do_not_generate_cpp_class) {
1083 flags |= ClassFlag::kGenerateCppClassDefinitions;
1084 }
1085 } else if (do_not_generate_cpp_class) {
1086 Lint("Annotation @doNotGenerateCppClass has no effect");
1087 }
1088
1089 // Filter to only include fields that should be present based on decoration.
1090 std::vector<ClassFieldExpression> fields;
1091 std::copy_if(
1092 fields_raw.begin(), fields_raw.end(), std::back_inserter(fields),
1093 [](const ClassFieldExpression& exp) {
1094 for (const ConditionalAnnotation& condition : exp.conditions) {
1095 if (condition.type == ConditionalAnnotationType::kPositive
1096 ? !BuildFlags::GetFlag(condition.condition, ANNOTATION_IF)
1097 : BuildFlags::GetFlag(condition.condition,
1098 ANNOTATION_IFNOT)) {
1099 return false;
1100 }
1101 }
1102 return true;
1103 });
1104
1105 std::vector<Declaration*> result;
1106
1107 result.push_back(MakeNode<ClassDeclaration>(
1108 name, flags, extends, generates, std::move(methods), fields,
1109 MakeInstanceTypeConstraints(annotations)));
1110
1111 Identifier* constexpr_name =
1112 MakeNode<Identifier>(CONSTEXPR_TYPE_PREFIX + name->value);
1113 constexpr_name->pos = name->pos;
1114 TypeExpression* constexpr_extends = AddConstexpr(extends);
1115 AbstractTypeFlags abstract_type_flags(AbstractTypeFlag::kConstexpr);
1116 if (transient) abstract_type_flags |= AbstractTypeFlag::kTransient;
1117 TypeDeclaration* constexpr_decl = MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1118 constexpr_name, abstract_type_flags, constexpr_extends,
1119 generates ? UnwrapTNodeTypeName(*generates) : name->value);
1120 constexpr_decl->pos = name->pos;
1121 result.push_back(constexpr_decl);
1122
1123 if ((flags & ClassFlag::kDoNotGenerateCast) == 0 &&
1124 (flags & ClassFlag::kIsShape) == 0) {
1125 ParameterList parameters;
1126 parameters.names.push_back(MakeNode<Identifier>("obj"));
1127 parameters.types.push_back(MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1128 std::vector<std::string>{}, MakeNode<Identifier>("HeapObject"),
1129 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}));
1130 LabelAndTypesVector labels;
1131 labels.push_back(LabelAndTypes{MakeNode<Identifier>("CastError"),
1132 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}});
1133
1134 TypeExpression* class_type = MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1135 std::vector<std::string>{}, name, std::vector<TypeExpression*>{});
1136
1137 std::vector<std::string> namespace_qualification{
1138 TORQUE_INTERNAL_NAMESPACE_STRING};
1139
1140 IdentifierExpression* internal_downcast_target =
1141 MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(
1142 namespace_qualification,
1143 MakeNode<Identifier>("DownCastForTorqueClass"),
1144 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{class_type});
1145 IdentifierExpression* internal_downcast_otherwise =
1146 MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
1147 MakeNode<Identifier>("CastError"));
1148
1149 Expression* argument = MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(
1150 std::vector<std::string>{}, MakeNode<Identifier>("obj"));
1151
1152 auto value = MakeCall(internal_downcast_target, base::nullopt,
1153 std::vector<Expression*>{argument},
1154 std::vector<Statement*>{MakeNode<ExpressionStatement>(
1155 internal_downcast_otherwise)});
1156
1157 auto cast_body = MakeNode<ReturnStatement>(value);
1158
1159 std::vector<TypeExpression*> generic_parameters;
1160 generic_parameters.push_back(MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1161 std::vector<std::string>{}, name, std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}));
1162
1163 Declaration* specialization = MakeNode<SpecializationDeclaration>(
1164 false, MakeNode<Identifier>("Cast"), generic_parameters,
1165 std::move(parameters), class_type, std::move(labels), cast_body);
1166 result.push_back(specialization);
1167 }
1168
1169 return ParseResult{result};
1170}

1385base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeEnumDeclaration(
1386 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
1387 const bool is_extern = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
1388 auto name_identifier = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
1389 auto name = name_identifier->value;
1390 auto base_type_expression =
1391 child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<TypeExpression*>>();
1392 auto constexpr_generates_opt =
1393 child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<std::string>>();
1394 auto entries = child_results->NextAs<std::vector<EnumEntry>>();
1395 const bool is_open = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
1396 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(
1397 child_results->matched_input().pos);
1398
1399 if (!is_extern) {
1400 ReportError("non-extern enums are not supported yet");
1401 }
1402
1403 if (!IsValidTypeName(name)) {
1404 NamingConventionError("Type", name, "UpperCamelCase");
1405 }
1406
1407 if (constexpr_generates_opt && *constexpr_generates_opt == name) {
1408 Lint("Unnecessary 'constexpr' clause for enum ", name);
1409 }
1410 auto constexpr_generates =
1411 constexpr_generates_opt ? *constexpr_generates_opt : name;
1412 const bool generate_nonconstexpr = base_type_expression.has_value();
1413
1414 std::vector<Declaration*> result;
1415 // Build non-constexpr types.
1416 if (generate_nonconstexpr) {
1417 DCHECK(base_type_expression.has_value());
1418
1419 if (is_open) {
1420 // For open enumerations, we define an abstract type and inherit all
1421 // entries' types from that:
1422 // type Enum extends Base;
1423 // namespace Enum {
1424 // type kEntry0 extends Enum;
1425 // ...
1426 // type kEntryN extends Enum;
1427 // }
1428 auto type_decl = MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1429 name_identifier, AbstractTypeFlag::kNone, base_type_expression,
1430 base::nullopt);
1431
1432 TypeExpression* name_type_expression =
1433 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(name_identifier);
1434 name_type_expression->pos = name_identifier->pos;
1435
1436 std::vector<Declaration*> entry_decls;
1437 entry_decls.reserve(entries.size());
1438 for (const auto& entry : entries) {
1439 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1440 entry.name, AbstractTypeFlag::kNone,
1441 entry.type.value_or(name_type_expression), base::nullopt));
1442 }
1443
1444 result.push_back(type_decl);
1445 result.push_back(
1446 MakeNode<NamespaceDeclaration>(name, std::move(entry_decls)));
1447 } else {
1448 // For closed enumerations, we define abstract types for all entries and
1449 // define the enumeration as a union of those:
1450 // namespace Enum {
1451 // type kEntry0 extends Base;
1452 // ...
1453 // type kEntryN extends Base;
1454 // }
1455 // type Enum = Enum::kEntry0 | ... | Enum::kEntryN;
1456 TypeExpression* union_type = nullptr;
1457 std::vector<Declaration*> entry_decls;
1458 for (const auto& entry : entries) {
1459 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1460 entry.name, AbstractTypeFlag::kNone,
1461 entry.type.value_or(*base_type_expression), base::nullopt));
1462
1463 auto entry_type = MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1464 std::vector<std::string>{name}, entry.name,
1465 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{});
1466 if (union_type) {
1467 union_type = MakeNode<UnionTypeExpression>(union_type, entry_type);
1468 } else {
1469 union_type = entry_type;
1470 }
1471 }
1472
1473 result.push_back(
1474 MakeNode<NamespaceDeclaration>(name, std::move(entry_decls)));
1475 result.push_back(
1476 MakeNode<TypeAliasDeclaration>(name_identifier, union_type));
1477 }
1478 }
1479
1480 // Build constexpr types.
1481 {
1482 // The constexpr entries inherit from an abstract enumeration type:
1483 // type constexpr Enum extends constexpr Base;
1484 // namespace Enum {
1485 // type constexpr kEntry0 extends constexpr Enum;
1486 // ...
1487 // type constexpr kEntry1 extends constexpr Enum;
1488 // }
1489 Identifier* constexpr_type_identifier =
1490 MakeNode<Identifier>(std::string(CONSTEXPR_TYPE_PREFIX) + name);
1491 TypeExpression* constexpr_type_expression = MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1492 MakeNode<Identifier>(std::string(CONSTEXPR_TYPE_PREFIX) + name));
1493 base::Optional<TypeExpression*> base_constexpr_type_expression =
1494 base::nullopt;
1495 if (base_type_expression) {
1496 base_constexpr_type_expression = AddConstexpr(*base_type_expression);
1497 }
1498 result.push_back(MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1499 constexpr_type_identifier, AbstractTypeFlag::kConstexpr,
1500 base_constexpr_type_expression, constexpr_generates));
1501
1502 TypeExpression* type_expr = nullptr;
1503 Identifier* fromconstexpr_identifier = nullptr;
1504 Identifier* fromconstexpr_parameter_identifier = nullptr;
1505 Statement* fromconstexpr_body = nullptr;
1506 if (generate_nonconstexpr) {
1507 DCHECK(base_type_expression.has_value());
1508 type_expr = MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
1509 MakeNode<Identifier>(name),
1510 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{});
1511
1512 // return %RawDownCast<Enum>(%FromConstexpr<Base>(o)))
1513 fromconstexpr_identifier = MakeNode<Identifier>("FromConstexpr");
1514 fromconstexpr_parameter_identifier = MakeNode<Identifier>("o");
1515 fromconstexpr_body =
1516 MakeNode<ReturnStatement>(MakeNode<IntrinsicCallExpression>(
1517 MakeNode<Identifier>("%RawDownCast"),
1518 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{type_expr},
1519 std::vector<Expression*>{MakeNode<IntrinsicCallExpression>(
1520 MakeNode<Identifier>("%FromConstexpr"),
1521 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{*base_type_expression},
1522 std::vector<Expression*>{MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(
1523 std::vector<std::string>{},
1524 fromconstexpr_parameter_identifier)})}));
1525 }
1526
1527 EnumDescription enum_description{CurrentSourcePosition::Get(), name,
1528 constexpr_generates, is_open};
1529 std::vector<Declaration*> entry_decls;
1530 for (const auto& entry : entries) {
1531 const std::string entry_name = entry.name->value;
1532 const std::string entry_constexpr_type =
1533 CONSTEXPR_TYPE_PREFIX + entry_name;
1534 std::string alias_entry;
1535 if (entry.alias_entry) {
1536 alias_entry = constexpr_generates + "::" + *entry.alias_entry;
1537 }
1538 enum_description.entries.emplace_back(
1539 constexpr_generates + "::" + entry_name, alias_entry);
1540
1541 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<AbstractTypeDeclaration>(
1542 MakeNode<Identifier>(entry_constexpr_type),
1543 AbstractTypeFlag::kConstexpr, constexpr_type_expression,
1544 constexpr_generates));
1545
1546 bool generate_typed_constant = entry.type.has_value();
1547 if (generate_typed_constant) {
1548 // namespace Enum {
1549 // const constexpr_constant_kEntry0: constexpr kEntry0 constexpr
1550 // 'Enum::kEntry0'; const kEntry0 = %RawDownCast<T,
1551 // Base>(FromConstexpr<Enum>(constexpr_constant_kEntry0));
1552 // }
1553 if (!generate_nonconstexpr) {
1554 Error(
1555 "Enum constants with custom types require an enum with an "
1556 "extends clause.")
1557 .Position((*entry.type)->pos);
1558 }
1559 Identifier* constexpr_constant_name =
1560 MakeNode<Identifier>("constexpr constant " + entry_name);
1561 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<ExternConstDeclaration>(
1562 constexpr_constant_name,
1563 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1564 std::vector<std::string>{},
1565 MakeNode<Identifier>(entry_constexpr_type),
1566 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}),
1567 constexpr_generates + "::" + entry_name));
1568 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<ConstDeclaration>(
1569 entry.name, *entry.type,
1570 MakeNode<IntrinsicCallExpression>(
1571 MakeNode<Identifier>("%RawDownCast"),
1572 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{*entry.type,
1573 *base_type_expression},
1574 std::vector<Expression*>{MakeCall(
1575 MakeNode<Identifier>("FromConstexpr"), {type_expr},
1576 {MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
1577 constexpr_constant_name)},
1578 {})})));
1579 } else {
1580 // namespace Enum {
1581 // const kEntry0: constexpr kEntry0 constexpr 'Enum::kEntry0';
1582 // }
1583 entry_decls.push_back(MakeNode<ExternConstDeclaration>(
1584 entry.name,
1585 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1586 std::vector<std::string>{},
1587 MakeNode<Identifier>(entry_constexpr_type),
1588 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}),
1589 constexpr_generates + "::" + entry_name));
1590 }
1591
1592 // FromConstexpr<Enum, Enum::constexpr kEntry0>(
1593 // : Enum::constexpr kEntry0): Enum
1594 if (generate_nonconstexpr) {
1595 TypeExpression* entry_constexpr_type_expr =
1596 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1597 std::vector<std::string>{name},
1598 MakeNode<Identifier>(entry_constexpr_type),
1599 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{});
1600
1601 ParameterList parameters;
1602 parameters.names.push_back(fromconstexpr_parameter_identifier);
1603 parameters.types.push_back(entry_constexpr_type_expr);
1604 result.push_back(MakeNode<SpecializationDeclaration>(
1605 false, fromconstexpr_identifier,
1606 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{type_expr, entry_constexpr_type_expr},
1607 std::move(parameters), type_expr, LabelAndTypesVector{},
1608 fromconstexpr_body));
1609 }
1610 }
1611
1612 result.push_back(
1613 MakeNode<NamespaceDeclaration>(name, std::move(entry_decls)));
1614 CurrentAst::Get().AddEnumDescription(std::move(enum_description));
1615 }
1616
1617 return ParseResult{std::move(result)};
1618}

1620base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeTypeswitchStatement(
1621 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
1622 auto expression = child_results->NextAs<Expression*>();
1623 auto cases = child_results->NextAs<std::vector<TypeswitchCase>>();
1624 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope matched_input_current_source_position(
1625 child_results->matched_input().pos);
1626
1627 // typeswitch (expression) case (x1 : T1) {
1628 // ...b1
1629 // } case (x2 : T2) {
1630 // ...b2
1631 // } case (x3 : T3) {
1632 // ...b3
1633 // }
1634 //
1635 // desugars to
1636 //
1637 // {
1638 // const _value = expression;
1639 // try {
1640 // const x1 : T1 = cast<T1>(_value) otherwise _NextCase;
1641 // ...b1
1642 // } label _NextCase {
1643 // try {
1644 // const x2 : T2 = cast<T2>(%assume_impossible<T1>(_value));
1645 // ...b2
1646 // } label _NextCase {
1647 // const x3 : T3 = %assume_impossible<T1|T2>(_value);
1648 // ...b3
1649 // }
1650 // }
1651 // }
1652
1653 BlockStatement* current_block = MakeNode<BlockStatement>();
1654 Statement* result = current_block;
1655 {
1656 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(expression->pos);
1657 current_block->statements.push_back(MakeNode<VarDeclarationStatement>(
1658 true, MakeNode<Identifier>("__value"), base::nullopt, expression));
1659 }
1660
1661 TypeExpression* accumulated_types;
1662 for (size_t i = 0; i < cases.size(); ++i) {
1663 CurrentSourcePosition::Scope current_source_position(cases[i].pos);
1664 Expression* value =
1665 MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(MakeNode<Identifier>("__value"));
1666 if (i >= 1) {
1667 value =
1668 MakeNode<AssumeTypeImpossibleExpression>(accumulated_types, value);
1669 }
1670 BlockStatement* case_block;
1671 if (i < cases.size() - 1) {
1672 value = MakeCall(MakeNode<Identifier>("Cast"),
1673 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{cases[i].type},
1674 std::vector<Expression*>{value},
1675 std::vector<Statement*>{MakeNode<ExpressionStatement>(
1676 MakeNode<IdentifierExpression>(
1677 MakeNode<Identifier>(kNextCaseLabelName)))});
1678 case_block = MakeNode<BlockStatement>();
1679 } else {
1680 case_block = current_block;
1681 }
1682 Identifier* name =
1683 cases[i].name ? *cases[i].name : MakeNode<Identifier>("__case_value");
1684 if (cases[i].name) name = *cases[i].name;
1685 case_block->statements.push_back(
1686 MakeNode<VarDeclarationStatement>(true, name, cases[i].type, value));
1687 case_block->statements.push_back(cases[i].block);
1688 if (i < cases.size() - 1) {
1689 BlockStatement* next_block = MakeNode<BlockStatement>();
1690 current_block->statements.push_back(
1691 MakeNode<ExpressionStatement>(MakeNode<TryLabelExpression>(
1692 MakeNode<StatementExpression>(case_block),
1693 MakeNode<TryHandler>(TryHandler::HandlerKind::kLabel,
1694 MakeNode<Identifier>(kNextCaseLabelName),
1695 ParameterList::Empty(), next_block))));
1696 current_block = next_block;
1697 }
1698 accumulated_types =
1699 i > 0 ? MakeNode<UnionTypeExpression>(accumulated_types, cases[i].type)
1700 : cases[i].type;
1701 }
1702 return ParseResult{result};
1703}

1790base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeTryLabelExpression(
1791 ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
1792 auto try_block = child_results->NextAs<Statement*>();
1793 CheckNotDeferredStatement(try_block);
1794 Statement* result = try_block;
1795 auto handlers = child_results->NextAs<std::vector<TryHandler*>>();
1796 if (handlers.empty()) {
1797 Error("Try blocks without catch or label don't make sense.");
1798 }
1799 for (size_t i = 0; i < handlers.size(); ++i) {
1800 if (i != 0 &&
1801 handlers[i]->handler_kind == TryHandler::HandlerKind::kCatch) {
1802 Error(
1803 "A catch handler always has to be first, before any label handler, "
1804 "to avoid ambiguity about whether it catches exceptions from "
1805 "preceding handlers or not.")
1806 .Position(handlers[i]->pos);
1807 }
1808 result = MakeNode<ExpressionStatement>(MakeNode<TryLabelExpression>(
1809 MakeNode<StatementExpression>(result), handlers[i]));
1810 }
1811 return ParseResult{result};

1840base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeCatchBlock(ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
1841 auto parameter_names = child_results->NextAs<std::vector<std::string>>();
1842 auto body = child_results->NextAs<Statement*>();
1843 for (const std::string& variable : parameter_names) {
1844 if (!IsLowerCamelCase(variable)) {
1845 NamingConventionError("Exception", variable, "lowerCamelCase");
1846 }
1847 }
1848 if (parameter_names.size() != 2) {
1849 ReportError(
1850 "A catch clause needs to have exactly two parameters: The exception "
1851 "and the message. How about: \"catch (exception, message) { ...\".");
1852 }
1853 ParameterList parameters;
1854
1855 parameters.names.push_back(MakeNode<Identifier>(parameter_names[0]));
1856 parameters.types.push_back(MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(
1857 std::vector<std::string>{}, MakeNode<Identifier>("JSAny"),
1858 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}));
1859 parameters.names.push_back(MakeNode<Identifier>(parameter_names[1]));
1860 parameters.types.push_back(MakeNode<UnionTypeExpression>(
1861 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
1862 MakeNode<Identifier>("JSMessageObject"),
1863 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{}),
1864 MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
1865 MakeNode<Identifier>("TheHole"),
1866 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{})));
1867 parameters.has_varargs = false;
1868 TryHandler* result = MakeNode<TryHandler>(
1869 TryHandler::HandlerKind::kCatch, MakeNode<Identifier>(kCatchLabelName),
1870 std::move(parameters), body);
1871 return ParseResult{result};
1872}

2098base::Optional<ParseResult> MakeClassField(ParseResultIterator* child_results) {
2099 AnnotationSet annotations(
2100 child_results,
2101 {ANNOTATION_CPP_RELAXED_STORE, ANNOTATION_CPP_RELAXED_LOAD,
2102 ANNOTATION_CPP_RELEASE_STORE, ANNOTATION_CPP_ACQUIRE_LOAD,
2103 ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_WEAK_MARKING},
2104 {ANNOTATION_IF, ANNOTATION_IFNOT});
2105 FieldSynchronization write_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kNone;
2106 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_RELEASE_STORE)) {
2107 write_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease;
2108 } else if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_RELAXED_STORE)) {
2109 write_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed;
2110 }
2111 FieldSynchronization read_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kNone;
2112 if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_ACQUIRE_LOAD)) {
2113 read_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kAcquireRelease;
2114 } else if (annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CPP_RELAXED_LOAD)) {
2115 read_synchronization = FieldSynchronization::kRelaxed;
2116 }
2117 std::vector<ConditionalAnnotation> conditions;
2118 base::Optional<std::string> if_condition =
2119 annotations.GetStringParam(ANNOTATION_IF);
2120 base::Optional<std::string> ifnot_condition =
2121 annotations.GetStringParam(ANNOTATION_IFNOT);
2122 if (if_condition.has_value()) {
2123 conditions.push_back({*if_condition, ConditionalAnnotationType::kPositive});
2124 }
2125 if (ifnot_condition.has_value()) {
2126 conditions.push_back(
2127 {*ifnot_condition, ConditionalAnnotationType::kNegative});
2128 }
2129 bool custom_weak_marking =
2130 annotations.Contains(ANNOTATION_CUSTOM_WEAK_MARKING);
2131 auto deprecated_weak = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
2132 if (deprecated_weak) {
2133 Error(
2134 "The keyword 'weak' is deprecated. For a field that can contain a "
2135 "normal weak pointer, use type Weak<T>. For a field that should be "
2136 "marked in some custom way, use @customWeakMarking.");
2137 custom_weak_marking = true;
2138 }
2139 auto const_qualified = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
2140 auto name = child_results->NextAs<Identifier*>();
2141 auto optional = child_results->NextAs<bool>();
2142 auto index = child_results->NextAs<base::Optional<Expression*>>();
2143 if (optional && !index) {
2144 Error(
2145 "Fields using optional specifier must also provide an expression "
2146 "indicating the condition for whether the field is present");
2147 }
2148 base::Optional<ClassFieldIndexInfo> index_info;
2149 if (index) {
2150 if (optional) {
2151 // Internally, an optional field is just an indexed field where the count
2152 // is zero or one.
2153 index = MakeNode<ConditionalExpression>(
2154 *index,
2155 MakeCall(
2156 MakeNode<Identifier>("FromConstexpr"),
2157 {MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
2158 MakeNode<Identifier>("intptr"),
2159 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{})},
2160 {MakeNode<IntegerLiteralExpression>(IntegerLiteral(1))}, {}),
2161 MakeCall(
2162 MakeNode<Identifier>("FromConstexpr"),
2163 {MakeNode<BasicTypeExpression>(std::vector<std::string>{},
2164 MakeNode<Identifier>("intptr"),
2165 std::vector<TypeExpression*>{})},
2166 {MakeNode<IntegerLiteralExpression>(IntegerLiteral(0))}, {}));
2167 }
2168 index_info = ClassFieldIndexInfo{*index, optional};
2169 }
2170 auto type = child_results->NextAs<TypeExpression*>();
2171 return ParseResult{ClassFieldExpression{{name, type},
2172 index_info,
2173 std::move(conditions),
2174 custom_weak_marking,
2175 const_qualified,
2176 read_synchronization,
2177 write_synchronization}};
2178}

2204struct TorqueGrammar : Grammar {
2205 static bool MatchWhitespace(InputPosition* pos) {
2206 while (true) {
2207 if (MatchChar(std::isspace, pos)) continue;
2208 if (MatchString("//", pos)) {
2209 while (MatchChar([](char c) { return c != '\n'; }, pos)) {
2210 }
2211 continue;
2212 }
2213 if (MatchString("/*", pos)) {
2214 while (!MatchString("*/", pos)) ++*pos;
2215 continue;
2216 }
2217 return true;
2218 }
2219 }
2220
2221 static bool MatchIdentifier(InputPosition* pos) {
2222 InputPosition current = *pos;
2223 MatchString("_", &current);
2224 if (!MatchChar(std::isalpha, &current)) return false;
2225 while (MatchChar(std::isalnum, &current) || MatchString("_", &current)) {
2226 }
2227 *pos = current;
2228 return true;
2229 }
2230
2231 static bool MatchAnnotation(InputPosition* pos) {
2232 InputPosition current = *pos;
2233 if (!MatchString("@", &current)) return false;
2234 if (!MatchIdentifier(&current)) return false;
2235 *pos = current;
2236 return true;
2237 }
2238
2239 static bool MatchIntrinsicName(InputPosition* pos) {
2240 InputPosition current = *pos;
2241 if (!MatchString("%", &current)) return false;
2242 if (!MatchIdentifier(&current)) return false;
2243 *pos = current;
2244 return true;
2245 }
2246
2247 static bool MatchStringLiteral(InputPosition* pos) {
2248 InputPosition current = *pos;
2249 if (MatchString("\"", &current)) {
2250 while (
2251 (MatchString("\\", &current) && MatchAnyChar(&current)) ||
2252 MatchChar([](char c) { return c != '"' && c != '\n'; }, &current)) {
2253 }
2254 if (MatchString("\"", &current)) {
2255 *pos = current;
2256 return true;
2257 }
2258 }
2259 current = *pos;
2260 if (MatchString("'", &current)) {
2261 while (
2262 (MatchString("\\", &current) && MatchAnyChar(&current)) ||
2263 MatchChar([](char c) { return c != '\'' && c != '\n'; }, &current)) {
2264 }
2265 if (MatchString("'", &current)) {
2266 *pos = current;
2267 return true;
2268 }
2269 }
2270 return false;
2271 }
2272
2273 static bool MatchHexLiteral(InputPosition* pos) {
2274 InputPosition current = *pos;
2275 MatchString("-", &current);
2276 if (MatchString("0x", &current) && MatchChar(std::isxdigit, &current)) {
2277 while (MatchChar(std::isxdigit, &current)) {
2278 }
2279 *pos = current;
2280 return true;
2281 }
2282 return false;
2283 }
2284
2285 static bool MatchIntegerLiteral(InputPosition* pos) {
2286 InputPosition current = *pos;
2287 bool found_digit = false;
2288 MatchString("-", &current);
2289 while (MatchChar(std::isdigit, &current)) found_digit = true;
2290 if (found_digit) {
2291 *pos = current;
2292 return true;
2293 }
2294 return false;
2295 }
2296
2297 static bool MatchFloatingPointLiteral(InputPosition* pos) {
2298 InputPosition current = *pos;
2299 bool found_digit = false;
2300 MatchString("-", &current);
2301 while (MatchChar(std::isdigit, &current)) found_digit = true;
2302 if (!MatchString(".", &current)) return false;
2303 while (MatchChar(std::isdigit, &current)) found_digit = true;
2304 if (!found_digit) return false;
2305 *pos = current;
2306 if ((MatchString("e", &current) || MatchString("E", &current)) &&
2307 (MatchString("+", &current) || MatchString("-", &current) || true) &&
2308 MatchChar(std::isdigit, &current)) {
2309 while (MatchChar(std::isdigit, &current)) {
2310 }
2311 *pos = current;
2312 return true;
2313 }
2314 return true;
2315 }
